## Summary
Design and implement the adapter architecture for bidirectional translation between tool-specific configs and canonical format.

## Context
From Council: "Each tool has its own config format. facult maintains bidirectional adapters. Version detection is worth it but keep it simpleтАФonly based on explicit version fields or reliable structural markers; otherwise fall back to latest with warnings."

## Requirements

### Directory structure
```
src/adapters/
тФЬтФАтФА index.ts              # Registry + dispatch
тФЬтФАтФА types.ts              # Shared types + interfaces
тФЬтФАтФА cursor/
тФВ   тФЬтФАтФА index.ts          # Cursor adapter
тФВ   тФФтФАтФА ...
тФЬтФАтФА claude/
тФВ   тФЬтФАтФА index.ts
тФВ   тФЬтФАтФА cli.ts            # Claude CLI specific
тФВ   тФФтФАтФА desktop.ts        # Claude Desktop specific
тФФтФАтФА ...
```

### ToolAdapter interface
```typescript
// src/adapters/types.ts

interface ToolAdapter {
  id: string;                    // 'cursor', 'claude-cli', etc.
  name: string;                  // 'Cursor', 'Claude CLI'
  versions: string[];            // ['1.0', '2.0']

  // Path detection
  getDefaultPaths(): ToolPaths;

  // Version detection (minimal, explicit fields only)
  detectVersion(configPath: string): Promise<string | null>;

  // Parse: tool format тЖТ canonical
  parseMcp(config: unknown, version?: string): CanonicalMcpConfig;
  parseSkills(skillsDir: string): Promise<CanonicalSkill[]>;

  // Generate: canonical тЖТ tool format
  generateMcp(canonical: CanonicalMcpConfig, version?: string): unknown;
  getSkillsSymlinkTarget(): string;  // Where to create symlinks
}

interface ToolPaths {
  mcp?: string;           // Path to MCP config file
  skills?: string;        // Path to skills directory
  config?: string;        // Path to main config (if separate)
}

interface CanonicalMcpConfig {
  servers: {
    [name: string]: {
      transport: 'stdio' | 'http' | 'sse';
      command?: string;
      args?: string[];
      url?: string;
      env?: Record<string, string>;
      vendorExtensions?: Record<string, unknown>;
    };
  };
}
```

### Adapter registry
```typescript
// src/adapters/index.ts

const adapters: Map<string, ToolAdapter> = new Map();

export function registerAdapter(adapter: ToolAdapter): void;
export function getAdapter(id: string): ToolAdapter | undefined;
export function getAllAdapters(): ToolAdapter[];
export function detectTool(path: string): ToolAdapter | undefined;
```

### Version detection rules
From Council: "Only detect when a version key exists; avoid heuristic drift."

1. Check for explicit version field in config
2. Check for known structural markers (field presence)
3. If undetectable, assume latest and log warning
4. Never use file modification dates for version detection

### Fallback behavior
```typescript
if (!detectedVersion) {
  console.warn(`Could not detect ${tool.name} version, assuming latest (${tool.versions[0]})`);
  return tool.versions[0];
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] ToolAdapter interface defined and documented
- [ ] Adapter registry works for register/get/detect
- [ ] Version detection attempts explicit fields first
- [ ] Clear warning when falling back to latest
- [ ] At least one adapter implemented as reference

## Effort
2 days

## Phase
Phase 4.5: Translation Layers
